-- #799: an EXPRESSION-level `let rec x = v in e2` (ELetGroup) with a non-function
-- RHS used to be SILENTLY ACCEPTED for the same reason as the block-level case —
-- inferLetGroup ran processLetGroup with no non-function check at all. Now
-- checkLetGroupBindsLocated mirrors the top-level guard here too. check == run ==
-- build all REJECT via a clean, LOCATED diagnostic, never a runtime panic.
main = println (let rec loop = loop in "unreachable")
